## 1b. DOCUMENTATION CONSISTENCY — mandatory when changing any ADR

**Rule: When you modify an ADR, you MUST check and update all ADRs it cross-references.**

The doc set is designed for "no developer questions" mode. A contradiction between ADRs means a
developer will guess — which means bugs. Before finishing any ADR change:

1. Read the "impacted by" list below for the ADR you changed.
2. Open each impacted ADR and verify the change doesn't contradict it.
3. If it does, update the impacted ADR with a dated note or corrected content.
4. Update this `.cursorrules` file if canonical values change.

