## 2. DATABASE SCHEMA (canonical: ADR-017 — docs are king)

**ADR-017 §8 DDL is the only schema source of truth.** `src/lib/sqlite.ts` and `migrations/` must converge to match ADR-017; never change ADR-017 to match incomplete code. Open compliance gaps: `documents/database/SCHEMA_RECONCILIATION.md` and `documents/no-developer-questions-build.md` §6–§7.

When verifying an existing database: `PRAGMA table_info(<table>)`. Known spec-not-yet-in-bootstrap (add migrations): `orders.tracking_number`, tables `activity_log`, `customer_notes`.

### `customers` table — flat billing address + ship-to via `addresses`
```
id, first_name, last_name, email, phone,
address_1, address_2, city, state, postal_code, country,
default_address_id, currency_code, is_active,
notes, created_at, updated_at
```

### `addresses` table — separate ship-to addresses (per customer, for orders)
```
id, customer_id, label, first_line, second_line,
city, state, postal_code, country, is_default,
created_at, updated_at
```

### `orders` table — order header with totals and ship-to snapshot
```
id, order_number, customer_id, order_date, order_status, payment_status,
was_paid, shipper, seller_shipping_cost, tracking_number,
shipped_without_paid_override, etsy_receipt_id, shipping_date,
ship_to_first_name, ship_to_last_name,
ship_to_address_line_1, ship_to_address_line_2,
ship_to_city, ship_to_state_province, ship_to_country, ship_to_postal_code,
subtotal, shipping_total, tax_total, discount_total, grand_total,
source_channel, notes,
easypost_shipment_id, label_url, label_format,
shipping_rate_cents, shipping_carrier_service,
created_at, updated_at
```
- `order_status`: active | void | cancelled
- `payment_status`: unpaid | paid | refunded
- `source_channel`: etsy | manual
- `tracking_number`: carrier tracking number (ADR-031)
- `easypost_shipment_id`: EasyPost shipment ID for label/refund (ADR-074)
- `label_url`: local path to purchased label PDF (ADR-074)
- `shipping_rate_cents`: postage cost in cents (ADR-074)
- `shipping_carrier_service`: carrier + service name (ADR-074)

### `order_items` table — line items per order
```
id, order_id, inventory_id, quantity, unit_price, line_total,
created_at, updated_at
```

### `purchases` table — BUY-SIDE only (vendor purchases of items to resell)
```
id, inventory_id, vendor_name, purchase_date, purchase_price,
shipping_price, reference_number, notes, created_at, updated_at
```
⚠️ NOTE: `purchases` = what Trudy BOUGHT from vendors, NOT customer sales.
Customer sales = `orders` + `order_items`.

### `inventory` table — full listing authoring fields included
```
id, item_number, description, purchase_cost, shipping_cost, sale_revenue,
date_purchased, date_listed, date_of_sale, shipping_date,
picture_1..picture_20, video_path, thumbnail_path,
condition_code, has_condition_issue, condition_notes, condition_picture_1..5,
status, etsy_listing_id,
etsy_when_made, etsy_taxonomy_id, etsy_who_made,
etsy_shipping_profile_id, etsy_return_policy_id,
quantity, category_tags, store_category,
materials, item_weight, item_weight_unit,
item_length, item_width, item_height, item_dimensions_unit,
is_supply, picture_classifications,
listing_title, listing_description, listing_tags, listing_category_path,
listing_title_strategy, listing_product_story, listing_condition_clarity,
listing_attributes, listing_pricing_shipping_notes, listing_quality_checklist,
listing_draft_state, listing_draft_source, listing_export_id,
listing_approved_at, listing_published_at, is_listed,
notes, created_at, updated_at
```
- `status`: Draft | In stock | Listed | Sold | Reserved | Retired
- `condition_code`: Mint/Near Mint | Excellent | Very Good | Good | Fair/As-Is
- `listing_draft_state`: draft | generated | imported | approved | published
- `listing_draft_source`: manual | integrated_ai | portable_import
- `etsy_when_made`: made_to_order | 2020_2026 | 2010_2019 | 2004_2009 | 2000_2003 | 1990s | 1980s | 1970s | 1960s | 1950s | 1940s | 1930s | 1920s | 1910s | 1900s | 1800s | 1700s | before_1700
- `etsy_who_made`: i_did | someone_else | collective (default `someone_else` for vintage)

### `settings` table — key/value store
Known keys: `etsy.active_shop_id`, `etsy.oauth.state`, `etsy.oauth.verifier`,
`etsy_access_token_encrypted`, `etsy_refresh_token_encrypted`, `etsy_token_expires_at`,
`app.session.current_id`, `panel_layout`, `default_shipper`,
`business_name`, `business_logo_path`, `report_header_logo_path`, `business_address_*`,
`pictures_matter_url`, `tutorial_system_folder_path`,
`last_etsy_sync_at`, `default_picture_directory`, `thumbnail_size`,
`outstanding_sort_*`, `date_format`, `first_day_of_week`,
`backup_directory`, `backup_schedule`, `shipping_info_usps/ups/fedex/dhl/other`,
`shipping.default_carrier` (ADR-034), `ui.date_format` (ADR-034),
`ui.page_size` (ADR-029/034), `ui.currency_code` (ADR-034),
`activity_log.retention_days` (ADR-037),
`tax.default_rate` (ADR-039), `setup.completed` (ADR-044),
`sync.auto_interval` (ADR-057), `last_integrity_check`, `integrity_warning` (ADR-058),
`repeat_customer_threshold` (ADR-066, optional)
`inventory.number_prefix` (item number auto-generation prefix, default "ITEM")
`inventory.number_padding` (item number zero-padding width, default 4, range 2-6)
`order.number_prefix` (order number auto-generation prefix, default "ORD")
`order.number_padding` (order number zero-padding width, default 4, range 2-6)
`inventory.store_categories` (comma-separated list of user-defined store categories for inventory),
`easypost.api_key_encrypted` (ADR-074), `easypost.address_validation` (ADR-074),
`easypost.label_format` (ADR-074), `easypost.label_size` (ADR-074),
`easypost.default_weight_oz` (ADR-074), `easypost.default_length_in` (ADR-074),
`easypost.default_width_in` (ADR-074), `easypost.default_height_in` (ADR-074),
`easypost.preferred_carrier` (ADR-074), `easypost.preferred_service` (ADR-074),
`etsy.publish.default_who_made` (ADR-017 §1b, default `someone_else`),
`etsy.publish.default_when_made` (ADR-017 §1a),
`etsy.publish.default_taxonomy_id` (ADR-017 §1c),
`etsy.publish.shipping_profile_id`, `etsy.publish.return_policy_id`,
`etsy.publish.readiness_state_id`,
`etsy.publish.image_max_dimension`, `etsy.publish.image_target_dpi`,
`etsy.publish.image_jpeg_quality`, `etsy.publish.allow_partial_image_upload`,
`etsy.publish.image_upload_attempts`,
`etsy_taxonomy.last_sync_at` (ISO timestamp of last taxonomy sync),
`etsy_taxonomy.node_count` (number of cached taxonomy nodes)

### `customer_notes` table — per-customer interaction log (ADR-065)
```
id, customer_id, note_text, note_type, created_at
```
- `note_type`: general | shipping_preference | communication | follow_up | complaint

### `etsy_receipts` table — raw Etsy receipt cache
```
id, receipt_id, shop_id, receipt_json, synced_at
```

### `listing_exports`, `listing_imports`, `listing_publish_previews` — listing workflow audit
```
listing_exports: id, export_id, inventory_id, payload_json, created_at
listing_imports: id, inventory_id, export_id, payload_json, source_label, created_at
listing_publish_previews: id, inventory_id, preview_hash, payload_json, created_at
```

### `other_costs` table — per-item additional costs
```
id, inventory_id, cost_type, amount, note, created_at, updated_at
```

### `activity_log` table — audit trail (ADR-037)
```
id, action, entity_type, entity_id, entity_label, detail_json, source, created_at
```
- `source`: `user` | `system` | `etsy_sync` (ADR-037 uses `etsy`; canonical is `etsy_sync`)
- Retention: 365 days (configurable via `activity_log.retention_days` setting)

### `report_artifacts` table — generated report metadata
```
id, report_name, report_params_json, artifact_path, artifact_json, generated_at
```

### `etsy_taxonomy_nodes` table — cached Etsy category tree
```
id (PK, from Etsy), parent_id, name, full_path, level
```

### `etsy_taxonomy_properties` table — cached Etsy per-category attributes
```
id, taxonomy_id, property_id, name, display_name,
is_required, supports_attributes, supports_variations,
possible_values_json, scales_json
UNIQUE(taxonomy_id, property_id)
```

### `api_call_log` table — external API call counter (ADR-075)
```
id, service, endpoint, status_code, created_at
```
- `service`: `etsy` | `openai` (future: `easypost`)
- Fire-and-forget logging; one row per outbound API call

---

## 3. API RULES

- All JSON errors use the standard envelope: `{ ok: false, error: { code, message, user_message, actions, can_retry }, fields? }`
- All list endpoints return: `{ items: [], pagination: { limit, offset, total, has_more } }`
- PATCH semantics: omitted = unchanged; null = clear field; empty string = empty string
- Status codes: 200 read/update, 201 created, 204 delete, 400 validation, 401 unauth, 404 not found, 409 conflict, 429 rate limit, 500 server error
- Protected routes: resolve session from HTTP-only cookie → SQLite settings `app.session.current_id`
- Date fields: `YYYY-MM-DD`; timestamps: ISO 8601 UTC
- Concurrent edit: 409 uses error code `CONCURRENT_EDIT` with `can_retry: true` (ADR-046, ADR-018)
- URL query params for lists: `sort_by`, `sort_dir`, `q`, `page`, `limit` (ADR-029)
- Per-order report URLs: path-based `/api/reports/invoice/[orderId]`, `/api/reports/thank-you/[orderId]`
- Tax rate stored as percentage number (e.g., `8.25` for 8.25%), not decimal fraction
- Full endpoint spec: `documents/adr/0018-api-surface-endpoints.md`

---

## 4. UI RULES

### Color system — always use CSS variables (defined in `src/app/globals.css`)
```
--ui-background: #081a34       (all screens)
--ui-panel-bg:   #0b2346       (header, panels, selects)
--ui-card-bg:    #0f2b55       (cards, sections)
--ui-border:     #1a3a66       (borders)
--ui-title:      #eef4ff       (headings)
--ui-body:       #c7d6f2       (body text)
--ui-muted:      #9bb0d1       (secondary)
--ui-green:      #00CC66       (success, paid, shipped)
--ui-yellow:     #FFCC00       (warning, unpaid)
--ui-red:        #FF4444       (error, danger)
--ui-accent:     #2f80ed       (primary buttons)
--ui-neutral:    #233553       (secondary buttons)
```
NEVER use hardcoded hex values in components. Always `var(--ui-*)` or Tailwind `bg-[var(--ui-*)]`.

### Layout structure (ADR-024 updated, ui-design.md §1)
- Tabs: top, full width — Dashboard | Sales | Inventory | Customers | Reports | Tutorial & Tips | Outstanding | Config
- **v1 layout:** Header + Tab bar + Main content (full width). No side panels.
- **Deferred to post-v1:** Commands panel and Outstanding side panel (ADR-009 notes)
- Header: app name, Etsy connection status, shop selector
- All pages use shared components: `Button`, `DataTable`, `FormField`, `Modal`, `Toast`, `EmptyState`, `LoadingSpinner`, `Badge`, `ErrorPanel` (ADR-028)
- Destructive actions use `ConfirmDialog` wrapper (ADR-032)

### Tabs and their commands: `documents/ui-design.md` §2 and §3 — read before building any tab

### Page layouts
- **Sales:** Master-detail — order list + order detail panel (ADR-031)
- **Inventory:** Two-panel — inventory detail + listing workshop (ADR-030)
- **No detail sub-routes:** Detail views are inline panels, NOT separate `[id]/page.tsx` routes (ADR-024)

### Outstanding behavior
- Full-page Outstanding tab (not a side panel in v1)
- Data-driven only (no user-added tasks)
- Server-side aggregation via `GET /api/outstanding` endpoint
- Click an item → deep-link navigate to correct tab with query param (ADR-035):
  - Orders → `/sales?orderId=<id>`
  - Inventory → `/inventory?itemId=<id>`
  - Customers → `/customers?customerId=<id>`
- Target page reads param, selects/scrolls to record, highlights, cleans URL
- Full definitions and queries: `documents/adr/0020-outstanding-list-definitions-and-queries.md`

### Forms and validation
- Errors always in user-friendly language (never expose DB or technical errors to UI)
- Primary action button always clearly visible
- Validation failures show field-level messages from the API `fields` object

---

## 5. BUSINESS LOGIC RULES — never guess, always check ADR-021 and design-decisions

### Key rules to always enforce:
- **Mark as shipped**: blocked until order is paid UNLESS user explicitly chooses "Ship anyway"
  → store `shipped_without_paid_override` audit flag on **orders** when overridden (ADR-021, ADR-040)
- **List on Etsy / publish**: blocked until listing_draft_state = 'approved' AND `etsy_when_made` set AND `etsy_taxonomy_id` set AND (`etsy_return_policy_id` or global default) AND (`etsy_shipping_profile_id` or global default)
- **Listing generation**: blocked until item has item_number + description + condition_code + sale_revenue > 0 + at least one picture
- **Can't list until complete**: listing_title + listing_description + listing_tags must all be non-empty
- **Publish-time field resolution**: per-item Etsy fields override global settings defaults (ADR-017 §1c)
- **Delete with purchases**: 409 if inventory item has associated order_items; can retire instead
- **Delete customer with orders**: 409 if customer has orders; cannot delete
- **Void/cancel order**: status change only, never delete rows; void/cancelled excluded from all reports
- **Etsy sync**: idempotent by receipt_id; never create duplicates
- **Token refresh**: proactive (5 min before expiry) + reactive (on 401); single in-flight; encrypted at rest (AES-256-GCM); per ADR-025

---

## 6. LISTING AUTHORING MODES (ADR-023)

Four modes — always respect all four:
1. **Manual** — guided form with sections: title strategy, product story, condition clarity, attributes, pricing/shipping notes, quality checklist
2. **Integrated AI** — app sends ALL pictures (picture_1..10 + condition_picture_1..5) + item context to AI provider; AI returns structured JSON saved to inventory
3. **Hybrid/Portable** — export package → user pastes into external AI → import JSON draft
4. **Listing Coach** (ADR-072) — 2-phase flow for new listings: log purchase + unified AI-populated editable form with per-field and global refinement

State machine: `draft → generated|imported → approved → published`
Only `approved` drafts can be published to Etsy.
Always send ALL non-empty pictures to AI — never generate listing content without full visual context.
Full spec: `documents/etsy-listing-template-and-requirements.md` and `documents/adr/0023-listing-content-generation-modes.md`

---

## 7. ETSY COMPLIANCE — always follow

- Use only the official Etsy API; no scraping
- OAuth 2.0 PKCE only; never expose tokens to client
- Respect rate limits; handle HTTP 429 + Retry-After gracefully
- Display trademark disclaimer: "The term 'Etsy' is a trademark of Etsy, Inc. This application uses the Etsy API but is not endorsed or certified by Etsy, Inc."
- No implied endorsement; app name clearly distinct from Etsy
- Full rules: `documents/etsy-compliance.md`

---

## 8. REPORTS

- All reports: PDF primary + CSV export from same data (exception: Accounting Export is CSV-only)
- User gets exactly 4 actions after generation: **Print | Export PDF | Export CSV | Cancel** (Accounting Export: **Export CSV | Cancel** only)
- Global data filter: only `order_status = 'active'` orders in all purchase/revenue reports
- Layout: 12pt Courier body, 14/16pt title, 1in margins, light grid, page numbers centered
- Report types: Thank You Note | Invoice | Sales | Costs | Income MTD | Income YTD | Postal by Vendor | Outstanding Items | AR Aging | Profit by Item | Sales Tax Summary | Inventory Aging | Accounting Export
- Full content spec per report type: `documents/adr/0013-report-output-pdf.md`

---

## 9. PICTURES AND FILE HANDLING

- **Frontend (ADR-033):** Visual 20-slot grid with drag-and-drop upload, file picker, thumbnail preview, drag-to-reorder
- **Backend (ADR-026):** File validation, Sharp processing, canonical storage paths, thumbnail generation
- Main pictures: picture_1..picture_20 (picture_1 = primary/hero; Etsy allows up to 20 per listing)
- Condition pictures: condition_picture_1..condition_picture_5
- Video: video_path (MP4/MOV, max 100 MB, 5–15 seconds; optional)
- Always show "Why pictures matter" link near any picture import UI
- Storage: paths stored in DB; files in `uploads/inventory/<item_id>/pictures/`; video in `uploads/inventory/<item_id>/video/`
- Thumbnail: JPEG, max 200px dimension; stored at `thumbnail_path`; auto-regenerated when picture_1 changes
- Allow: JPEG, PNG, WebP, GIF; reject others; max 15 MB per file
- Image serving: `GET /api/uploads/[...path]` (ADR-018 §16, ADR-033)
- Full spec: `documents/adr/0026-picture-storage-and-thumbnails.md` (backend) + `documents/adr/0033-image-upload-and-thumbnail-preview.md` (frontend)

---

## 10. SHIPPING LABELS

- NO automated connection to any carrier API — ever
- App generates label from: order ship-to address + stored Shipping Info (from Config)
- If Shipping Info missing for chosen carrier: block label, tell user "Go to Config → Shipping Info"
- Shipping Info stored in settings: `shipping_info_usps`, `shipping_info_ups`, etc.
- Full behavior: `documents/shipping-label-carrier-templates.md`

---

## 11. CODE STYLE

- TypeScript strict mode — no `any` types unless absolutely unavoidable
- Next.js App Router patterns — no Pages Router patterns
- All DB access: parameterized queries only — no string interpolation in SQL
- All API routes: return standard error envelope on failure
- All user-facing error messages: plain English, actionable, never expose stack traces
- Tailwind for styling; CSS variables for colors; no hardcoded hex
- No `console.log` in production paths; use `src/lib/logging.ts` structured logger
- Never commit secrets; all credentials via env vars

