## 13. NEVER DO THESE

- Never use hardcoded hex colors — use CSS variables
- Never expose OAuth tokens, API keys, or session secrets to the client
- Never delete purchase/order rows — void/cancel by status change only
- Never generate listing content without sending ALL item pictures to the AI
- Never allow publish-to-Etsy unless listing_draft_state = 'approved'
- Never allow Mark as shipped without paid check (or explicit override + audit flag)
- Never connect to carrier APIs (USPS, UPS, FedEx, DHL) — label generation is local only
- Never cache Etsy HTTP API responses for reuse (per Etsy API Terms). The `etsy_receipts` table is operational data persistence, not caching.
- Never scrape Etsy or bypass the official API
- Never use string interpolation in SQL queries
- Never expose stack traces or DB errors in user-facing messages
- Never break the standard API error envelope shape
